File: The Power utility is urging people to use electricity sparingly as the system faces enormous pressure. JOHANNESBURG - City Power has confirmed there's a high possibility of load reduction in parts of the city. This as the power grid continues to be under severe restraint due to illegal connections. READ: Eskom announces load reduction in Limpopo and Mpumalanga The load rotation will take place in high-density areas, every day between 16h00 and 22h00. Eskom has also warned of a high probability of load-shedding if the system continues to be overloaded. Residents are urged to use electricity sparingly.